'''Alfred E. Lewis''', better known as "Al Lewis", (ca. 1913 – 1994<ref name=wpobit/>) was an American [[journalist]], best known as the author of the first ''[[Washington Post]]'' article about the burglary at [[Watergate]].<ref name=wpobit>Martin Weil, [https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/1994/05/04/legendary-police-reporter-alfred-e-lewis-dies/9b9b495d-d268-409b-9dfd-9e1a39db320f/ "Legendary Police Reporter Alfred E. Lewis Dies"], ''The Washington Post'', May 4, 1994</ref>

